-- EU Needs ‘Full-Fledged’ Financial Union, Portugal’s Gaspar Says
-- B y   K a s i a   K l i m a s i n s k a
-- 2013-03-26T15:06:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-26/eu-needs-full-fledged-financial-union-portugal-s-gaspar-says.html
The European Union needs a “full-
fledged” financial union, Portugal’s Finance Minister Vitor
Gaspar said.  The lack of a common system leads to the situation in which
the transmission of monetary policy doesn’t work appropriately,
Gaspar said today in a presentation at the  Brookings Institution 
in Washington.  To contact the reporter on this story:
